    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is accepted under a risk-informed rationale: model risk level is 3 (medium), model influence is medium, and the single test condition is the regulatory standard (ASTM F1717). All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for the stated COU.",
